The actor, 59, put 780 prints from his debut pop art collection - Friends And Heroes - on sale through Castle Fine Art in London. They depict four people who have inspired him: Keith Richards,Al Pacino, Bob Dylan and Liz Taylor. Framed images sold for £3,950 individually while all four together set fans back £14,950.  After Depp's six-week court battle with ex-wife Heard in the US, the jury awarded her £1.5million in damages.